hopobject.body: I came here to study positionhealth.com InSight is equipped with a heat-flow probe, which it will hammer into the surface of Mars to a depth of between 9 and 15 feet (2.7 to 4.5 meters). But the probe can only hammer into Martian dirt and broken-up surface material, not hard bedrock. InSight also carries a seismometer and radio to conduct experiments. Scientists hope the mission will help them better understand how rocky planets form.
